profileDescription: I'm Seif El-Deen Mostafa, I'm a Software Engineer at Psystems Company, I graduated from the faculty of computer and information systems Ain-Shams University, I'm interested in Data Analytics, Flutter Development, .Net Development, I took 3 Data Analysis tracks from DataCamp using  Power Bi, Python and SQL. I also got 4 certificates in flutter development and developed more than 15 projects using flutter framework, by the way this website is developed using flutter.

projects.description: A Dashboard about a hospital that have many branches and wants to analise the occupation of it's rooms over the year, and also to take care about the rating of every branch according to it's occupation.

A Dashboard made for an hr to see the percentage of employees who prefers to work from home and how prefers to work onsite, also to keep track on the rate of sick leave (during the corona virus period).

A dashboard about the olympic games from 1896 to 2016 where the number of competitors is counted, total number of medals over the years, number of medals grouped by sport and categorized by type of medal, a bar char that displays the number of medals that each athlete toke.

A dashboard using Power Bi, the dashboard is for a pizza store so by interacting with the dashboard the stackholders can find the most  & least sold items, their amounts, total revenue and some more things that can help them take decisions.

A dashboard using Power Bi, made on a data collected from the people working in the data fields visualising their countries, their average age, their average rate of happiness, and the jobs with the highest salaries.

One of the simple projects that I developed it's UI as I seen it the one of the courses (The Complete Flutter Developement Guide), using dummy data, the app consists of categories each category consists of a list of meals and you can see the description of each meal, you can also make filter that filters the food according to your choice, you can put your favorite meals in the favorite list so it is easier to access them.

I developed this application as I learned it in one of the courses (The complete 2021 flutter & dart development course), the app consists of 3 screens and a bottom sheet where you can add a new task and change it's place from the new tasks to the done tasks or the archived tasks or you can remove it from the app at all, the data is stored to a local database (sqlite package).
A Simple Notes App, I took the design of the app from one of the courses that I learned.

This was my first flutter application, I have created it to apply all the things that I learned at this time, the app consists of four pages the main page where you navigate to play a game or choose to navigate to one of the other 2 screens, one of them give you a brief description on how to play the game and the other one is just a contact page.
A Simple Application that helps the people suffering from diabetes to record the suger level in their blood, Using hive package as a local storage.

The idea of ths application is very simple you can create a bag(Work Bag, School Bag, etc.) inside each bag you can add your items like(pen, pencil, notebook, laptop, etc.), you can delete a bag or a specific item inside a bag, you can also edit the name of the items, there is also a way to check that you forgot nothing by checking the correct button in the right of each item, once all your bag is done a pop up message will appear that tells you that your bag is ready and you forgot nothing.

A simple chatting App that I developed using flutter framework where the users can register or sign in, I used firebase for authentication and data storage, I also used the provider package for state management

This was my graduation project, We developed it using flutter framework, our application consists of two main parts: First part the learning part where the user can use it to learn the basics of the Arabic sign language. Second part is the translation part where the user can upload a video or capture a video then the video is sent to the server to translate it and returns the response back in the form of Arabic text( handled using API request).
